First off, the HTML isn't rendering correctly. "Col 1" has text in-between the table cells. This text ends up getting rendered outside of the table, at least in Chrome. Also, the `<tbody>` at the end of the table should be a closing `</tbody>` or the table gets an extra empty tbody added.

As a quick aside, in this fork of tablesorter, the `ipAddress` parser was moved into the separate `parser-network.js` file to make way for the now built-in image parser. 

The built-in image parser looks in the attribute set by the [`imgAttr` option](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#imgattr). If not set, it falls back to `"alt"`. If the image doesn't have anything set in the attribute, the parser uses the table cell text instead. In [this demo](https://jsfiddle.net/bbxxomhx/383/), the alt text is added, but the number and time in the image column are completely ignored.

```js
$(function() {
  $('table').tablesorter({
    theme: 'blue',
    imgAttr: 'alt', // default setting
    widgets: ['filter', 'zebra']
  });
});
```

To include the text from the image cell, you'll need to write a custom parser - [demo](https://jsfiddle.net/bbxxomhx/385/):

HTML (this sets the custom parser)

```html
<th class="sorter-image-and-text">happy II sad</th>
```

JS

```js
$(function() {

  $.tablesorter.addParser({
    id: 'image-and-text',
    is: function() {
      return false;
    },
    format: function(str, table, cell) {
      return ($(cell).find('img').attr(table.config.imgAttr || 'alt') || '') + str;
    },
    // filter widget flag; true = always use parsed data
    parsed: true,
    type: 'text'
  });

  $('table').tablesorter({
    theme: 'blue',
    imgAttr: 'alt', // default setting
    widgets: ['filter', 'zebra']
  });

});
```

