@SylvainCorlay, @minrk, if we decide not to cross-validate default values, then we probably shouldn't validate them at all. One alternative would be to pass default validators a `Bunch` containing the trait. Thus a user could defined:

```python
@default
_my_default(self, init):
    # ... make a default
    return init.trait.validate(self, value)
```

Here it's up to the user to ensure that there are no circular dependencies between they're traits.

